🏠 HouseHunt: Finding Your Perfect Rental Home
🔶 Project Summary:
HouseHunt is a web-based application that helps users search, filter, 
and compare rental properties based on location, budget, number of rooms, amenities, and user preferences. 
It uses a combination of a clean UI, geolocation services, and optional machine learning for personalized recommendations.
🧰 Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (optionally React or Vue.js)

Backend: Flask or Django

Database: SQLite / PostgreSQL

ML (Optional): Scikit-learn / Pandas / NumPy

Hosting: Render, Heroku, or Vercel (frontend)

🔄 Core Features
🔍 Search rental listings by city, price, type

🧩 Filter by bedrooms, amenities, pet-friendly, etc.

🗺️ Map integration (Google Maps API / Leaflet)

❤️ Save favorite properties

🧠 Personalized recommendations (ML model)

👤 User login/registration (optional)
📘 1. Project Objective
To build a smart rental home discovery platform that allows users to find, filter, and receive
personalized recommendations for rental properties based on their preferences (location, budget, rooms, amenities, etc.).

🎯 2. Key Features
Feature	Description
🔍 Property Search	Search homes by location, rent, type
🧩 Advanced Filters	Filter by price, number of rooms, pet-friendly, furnished, etc.
📍 Map Integration	Visual display using Leaflet or Google Maps API
❤️ Save Favorites	Add/remove properties to a wishlist
🔐 User Authentication	Login/register to manage saved searches
🤖 ML-Powered Recommendations	Suggest rentals based on user history and preferences
📱 Responsive UI	Mobile-friendly layout
📦 REST API	Backend handles property data, ML, and user actions

⚙️ 3. Technologies Used
Frontend:
ReactJS (or Vanilla JS + HTML/CSS)

Tailwind CSS / Bootstrap

Leaflet / Google Maps API

Backend:
Flask (Python) or Django

Flask-RESTful for APIs

SQLite (Dev) / PostgreSQL (Prod)

Machine Learning:
Scikit-learn

Pandas

KNN Recommender / Clustering

Hosting:
Frontend: Vercel / Netlify

Backend: Render / Railway / Heroku

Database: Supabase / SQLite
🔒 9. Optional Add-ons
Feature	Tool/Library
Login/Auth	Firebase Auth / Flask-JWT
